accessKey

public String accessKey
The Google APIs Access key. This identifies your application for analytics and quota purposes. To create an accessKey for your application, see the identity section of the Google APIs developer console.

baseServer

public String baseServer
Server hosting the API, for example "https://www.googleapis.com/". This is determined when the library is generated, but may be changed to use an alternate server, typically during testing of a new service.

basePath

public String basePath
Base path of service on server, for example "/moderator/v1/". Must be URL-encoded. This is determined when the library is generated and normally should not be changed.

prettyPrint

public Boolean prettyPrint
Add the prettyPrint flag to server requests so that the response is formatted for readability. This makes debugging easier at the expense of slightly larger request sizes. The default is to use the server default, which is usually to pretty print.
